deleted: Prior to 2018, during the course of his years at the Carlyle Group, Youngkin served on the boards of directors of numerous Carlyle portfolio companies.<ref name="8-K Oct 2017"/>

As of 2021, he is on the National Council of the [[American Enterprise Institute]].<ref>{{cite web |title=National Council |url=https://www.aei.org/about/national-council/ |website=[[American Enterprise Institute]] |access-date=February 21, 2021}}</ref> He is a member of the [[The Business Council]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Member List |url=https://businesscouncil.com/member-list/char/Y/ |website=[[The Business Council]] |access-date=February 21, 2021}}</ref> and a member of the [[Council on Foreign Relations]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Membership Roster |url=https://www.cfr.org/membership/roster |website=[[Council on Foreign Relations]] |access-date=February 21, 2021}}</ref>
